  "text": "We decrease epsilon from 1.0 to 0.1, and we have tried different epsilon schedules and found that with a longer ex- ploration and exploitation process, the result will get better as shown in Figure 3 , green line with a shorter exploration and exploitation process but blue with longer, any other setting is same. This is because the searching space will be larger and the agent can see more block structures in the random exploration period. Table 2 shows that the number of unique minibatch we trained at different epsilon. We maintain a replay memory same as [CITATION_1] , after each minibatch is sampled and trained, the agent randomly samples 128 blocks from the memory dictionary and applies the Q-value update for 64 times.",
